  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Jasper</strong></p>
<p>There is an excellent ski school and plenty of gentle runs around the base area. With easy runs accessible from most lifts you will soon be exploring the ski area.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in Jasper</strong></p>
<p>Intermediates Marmot’s great mix of terrain make it ideal for intermediate skiers. Try Paradise or Marmot run for fantastic views of the Athabasca Valley.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Jasper</strong></p>
<p>There are hundreds of acres of Black Diamond terrain and once you have “skied the Knob” you may count yourself amongst the privileged skiers that have experienced the best of Canadian bowls, chutes and powder.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in Jasper</strong></p>
<p>Ideal for boarders of all level who will enjoy the varied terrain, powder snow and the park offering variety of jumps and rails.</p>]]></generalInformation>
